r","text":"Absolutely. Clinics can configure one or multiple lab partners within their Virtual Practice. Lab admins can assign orders to the right partner, and results uploaded by the lab automatically update the patient's medical record."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How are lab results shared with patients and providers?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"When a lab partner uploads results against a service request, the files are securely stored in the patient's medical record. Both the patient and provider can access the results through their Virtual Practice interfaces."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Who manages lab orders within the clinic?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"The Lab Admin role has full oversight. Lab admins get notified whenever a new order is generated, can assign service requests to lab partners, and ensure timely processing."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can the Virtual Practice handle billing for lab orders?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. Lab partners can generate bills for lab order fulfilment. Currently, these bills are issued to the clinic (the customer), not directly to the patient."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is the Lab Orders feature powered by AI?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"No. The Lab Orders feature in the Virtual Practice is not AI-driven. Its value lies in the seamless, secure, and transparent flow of information between providers, patients, and lab partners."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Why should a clinic or healthcare startup use the Virtual Practice for lab orders?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Because it eliminates paperwork, ensures patients never lose access to their orders or results, and integrates lab fulfilment into the broader patient record — making care delivery more connected and efficient."}}]}</script><section class="py-16 bg-gray-50"><div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8"><div class="text-center mb-12"><h2 class="text-3xl md:te